%N A394189 Number of partitions of n such that (number of distinct parts) < minimal multiplicity of the parts.
%H A394189 Seiichi Manyama, <a href="/A394189/b394189.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000</a>
%F A394189 G.f.: Sum_{j>=0} [z^j] Product_{k>=1} (1 + z*q^((j+1)*k)/(1-q^k)).
%e A394189 a(12) = 8 counts these partitions: 66, 444, 3333, 333111, 222222, 22221111, 222111111, 111111111111.
%o A394189 (PARI) my(N=70, q='q+O('q^N)); Vec(sum(j=0, N, polcoef(prod(k=1, N, 1+z*q^((j+1)*k)/(1-q^k)), j, z)))
